info:
Schemas can be split across files and chained together with `import` statements. `sensor.proto` is the root:

```proto
import "common.proto";
import "location.proto";

message SensorReport {
    Header header = 1;
    Location location = 2;
    double value = 3;
}
```

The protobuf-file config node lists **only the root file** - protobuf.js loads `common.proto` and `location.proto` automatically because they are imported and live in the same folder. (Comma-separated paths are still available for loading unrelated files side by side.)

Click the inject button: the nested payload is encoded into one `SensorReport` message and decoded back, including the `Header` and `Location` types that come from the imported files.

The protobuf-file config node points at:

    node_modules/@pauldeng/node-red-contrib-protobuf/examples/protos/sensor.proto

This relative path works when Node-RED runs from your user directory (for example `~/.node-red`). If the proto file fails to load, open the protobuf-file config node and enter the absolute path on your machine.
